citeinfo.title: PacificCrestTrail

descript.abstract:
This feature class captures the Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail (PCT) from start to finish. The PCT spans 2,650 miles from the US-Mexican border to the US-Canadian border. It traverses through multiple land-ownerships across three western states: California, Oregon and Washington.
The USDA Forest Service is the lead managing agency for the Pacific Crest National Scenic Trail (PCT). The USDA Forest Service Region 5, Pacific Southwest Region, provides management oversight to the PCT GIS data layers.
descript.purpose: To provide a base layer for U.S. Forest Service GIS and applications.
